<br><br>
We seem to have digressed a little into Spatzoid issues, for which I, too, am guilty. That last Spatzoid outburst has a lot of &quot;analyst's delight&quot; stuff. Perhaps it belongs on another thread, or on a planet in a solar system in an alternative universe. <br><br>
I would like to see us back on the PTSD track because I, for one, was really getting something out of it. It is not very often that all this horsepower and experience digs into this topic, one that is so germain to the Vietnam War and 'NamVets.<br><br>
MTF mentions &quot;intimacy Vs. isolation&quot; as a theorized fifth level of human development. Like Tom, I was 22-23 years old when I was in 'Nam, but I did not fare as well. There are probably more individual factors that could predispose one to PTSD, or, as was suggested with Cook's handling of things, individual factors of specific training and background that could push it away.<br><br>
I am finding that the more I consider about this thing in my head, a thing that seems to have a life and personality of its own sometimes, the better I can come to grips with the reality of it all. Compensatory mechanisms I am now learning seem to make more sense in light of it all!
